### Proposal

Under scss/mixins/_forms.scss

I believe this is where the code change should be.

```scss
@mixin form-validation-state(
  $state,
  $color,
  $icon,
  $tooltip-color: color-contrast($color),
  $tooltip-bg-color: rgba($color, $form-feedback-tooltip-opacity),
  $focus-box-shadow: 0 0 $input-btn-focus-blur $input-focus-width rgba($color, $input-btn-focus-color-opacity)
) {
  .form-control {
    @include form-validation-state-selector($state) {
      // I'm proposing to change this rule to be !important which it currently isn't.
      border-color: $color !important;
    }
  }
}
```

### Motivation and context

See the code comment about making this rule !important

I propose this as this would allow to set your own non-validated default border-color outside of bootstrap. (I'm not sure if this is possible otherwise?) 
Bootstrap having the !important rule would override the default border color set outside of bootstrap when validating (which is what we want)
If it doesn't have !important, the validation border color gets overridden by the non-validated border color set outside bootstrap.

